Olaide Oyelude, Katsina The National Youths Service Corps has begun the construction of a new pavilion at its permanent orientation camp in Katsina State. When completed, the new pavilion will cater to the corps members during lectures and other activities to be held at the orientation camp located along the Mani Road. The NYSC Coordinator in Katsina State, Alhaji Ahidjo Yahaya, who confirmed the development on Sunday, said the new pavilion was part of his commitment to improve infrastructural development at the camp. “We are embarking on the construction of a new pavilion to provide support to the existing one following the increase in the population of corps members deployed in the state,” he stated. Our correspondent observed that the construction of the structure had reached an advanced stage. A total of 2,145 Batch ‘A’, Stream 1 corps members are currently in the state for the 2020 national service. The figure is made up of 1,028 males and 1,117 females. ”Copyright PUNCH.
